<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <p class="text-center">Getme is known for its disruption of well-established industries through technological innovation and mass scale. The company initially started as an online marketplace for books but later expanded to sell electronics, software, video games, apparel, furniture, food, toys, and jewelry. Get me was founded in 2020. The company which managed the inventory of individuals selling their belongings through the company internet site. The platform employs browsing technologies which personalise shopping visually for each customer, rather than relying on a search bar format. It allows sellers to list their products on Getme and sell directly to consumers</p>
        <p class="text-center">As the company expanded product categories beyond collectibles into almost any saleable item, business grew quickly. The company's business strategy includes increasing the online trade.In 2020, Getme announced the opening of it`s office at Empire State building in New York.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="embed-responsive embed-responsive-16by9">
            <iframe class="embed-responsive-item" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/yZpA5w6cjcU" allowfullscreen></iframe>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<br />
<br />
<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-2">
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-4">
        <div class="card testimonial-card text-white bg-secondary mt-2 mb-3">
            <div class="card-up aqua-gradient"></div>
            <div class="avatar mx-auto white">
                <img src="http://res.cloudinary.com/teodorascloud/image/upload/bv1wzm5rjfbnevhwfxdo.jpg" class="rounded-circle img-responsive" style="overflow:hidden; height:220px; width:220px; border-radius:50%;" alt="woman avatar">
            </div>
            <div class="card-body text-white bg-secondary">
                <h4 class="card-title font-weight-bold">Martha Smith</h4>
                <h6 class="card-title font-weight-bold warning"><em>Founder</em></h6>
                <hr>
                <p><i class="fas fa-quote-left warning"></i> Start by doing what's necessary, then what's possible; and suddenly you are doing the impossible.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-4">
        <div class="card testimonial-card text-white bg-secondary mt-2 mb-3">
            <div class="card-up aqua-gradient"></div>
            <div class="avatar mx-auto white">
                <img src="http://res.cloudinary.com/teodorascloud/image/upload/bwkku3iisjssbfkvvyho.jpg" class="rounded-circle img-responsive" style="overflow:hidden; height:220px; width:220px; border-radius:50%;" alt="woman avatar">
            </div>
            <div class="card-body text-white bg-secondary">
                <h4 class="card-title font-weight-bold">John Robertson</h4>
                <h6 class="card-title font-weight-bold warning"><em>Marketing manager</em></h6>
                <hr>
                <p><i class="fas fa-quote-left warning"></i> Our jobs as marketers are to understand how the customer wants to buy and help them to do so.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-2">
    </div>
</div>



@section MainNavigation {

    @if (HttpContextAccessor.HttpContext.Session.GetString("CurrentUser") != null)
    {
        <li class="nav-item">
            <a class="nav-link text-light" asp-area="" asp-controller="Registry" asp-action="Registry">Registry</a>
        </li>
        @if (HttpContextAccessor.HttpContext.Session.GetString("CurrentUserIsAdmin") == "true")
        {
            <li class="nav-item">
                <a class="nav-link text-light" asp-area="Admin" asp-controller="Categories" asp-action="Categories">Buy</a>
            </li>

        }
        else
        {
            <li class="nav-item">
                <a class="nav-link text-light" asp-area="" asp-controller="Categories" asp-action="Categories">Buy</a>
            </li>
        }
        <li class="nav-item">
            <a class="nav-link text-light" asp-area="" asp-controller="Sell" asp-action="Sell">Sell</a>
        </li>
    }
}

@section AccountNavigation {
    @if (HttpContextAccessor.HttpContext.Session.GetString("CurrentUser") != null)
    {
        <li>
            <a class="nav-link text-light" asp-area="" asp-controller="Profile" asp-action="Profile" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="top" title="Profile"><i class="fas fa-user-circle fa-2x warning"></i></a>
        </li>
        <li>
            <a class="nav-link text-light" asp-area="" asp-controller="ShoppingCart" asp-action="ShoppingCart" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="top" title="Shopping Cart"><i class="fas fa-shopping-cart fa-2x warning"></i></a>
        </li>
        <li>
            <a class="nav-link text-light" asp-area="" asp-controller="Account" asp-action="LogOut" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="top" title="Sign out"><i class="fas fa-sign-out-alt fa-2x"></i></a>
        </li>

    }
    else
    {
        <li>
            <a class="nav-link text-light" asp-area="" asp-controller="Account" asp-action="LogIn">Sign in</a>
        </li>
        <li>
            <a class="nav-link text-light" asp-area="" asp-controller="Account" asp-action="Register">Register</a>
        </li>
    }
}

<script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/animejs/2.0.2/anime.min.js"></script>
<script src="~/js/pageTitle.js"></script>
